@Hamodee - I labeled this torrent "1080p" so that folks understand it can be played back on a computer or device - including those listed in the description - that supports video files with image dimensions up to 1920x1080 and running at 23.98 frames per second. 

All my torrents say "iTunes" so that people know what universe it's meant for (my files are .m4v extension instead of the AVI, MKV or MP4 files that other uploaders post) and what features to expect (video is AVC or MPEG-4, must have a AAC audio track, subtitles must be text-based, etc)

